---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import mainCatGif from '../assets/global/main-cat.gif';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>üëã Welcome to my‚Ä¶ blog?</h1>
			<p>
				Well, not exactly. I'd call it more of a collection of HowTo Tutorials.
			</p>
			<p>
				I've always struggled to find guides that are both clear and practical-something with real examples + screenshots.<br><br>
				Personally, I learn way faster when I see how things are done, instead of just reading walls of text ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è
			</p>
			<p>
				So I thought myself: why not create the kind of tutorials I always wanted, and share them here?
			</p>
			<p>
				I hope you find something useful (<i>good thing ChatGPT can't argue with my screenshot tutorials</i>üòÅ)
			</p>
			<div class="cat-gif">
				<img src={mainCatGif.src} alt="Pop cat gif" />
			</div>
			<div class="ps-block">
				<p>
					P.S. This blog is open-source!<br><br>
					If you notice something that could be explained better, or you've got an idea for improvement, feel free to jump in. I'll happily review your Pull Request
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.cat-gif {
		text-align: center;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}
	
	.cat-gif img {
		max-width: 200px;
		height: auto;
		border-radius: 8px;
	}
	
	.ps-block {
		margin: 2rem 0;
		padding: 0 0 0 1.5rem;
		font-style: italic;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		background: none;
		border-style: dashed;
		border-color: rgb(219, 219, 219);
		text-align: center;
	}
</style>
